==English==

===Etymology===
Prefix "pan-" (greek 'pas', 'pantos'= "all") and "tropical" (from greek 'tropikos', referring to where the length of the day equals that of the night)

===Adjective===
# biology, pertaining to area of geographical occurrence. Literally: occurring in all the tropical regions. Usage: occurring in the tropics of Africa, Asia and America.

